and see how the glory of the Lord

502
00:25:46,939 --> 00:25:48,539
would fill the house of God.

503
00:25:48,539 --> 00:25:50,819
Of course, the tabernacle there

504
00:25:50,819 --> 00:25:52,899
during the ministry and life of Moses,

505
00:25:52,899 --> 00:25:55,019
it was David that had the desire

506
00:25:55,019 --> 00:25:56,619
to build the temple.

507
00:25:56,619 --> 00:25:58,979
And you remember that David had that desire

508
00:25:58,979 --> 00:26:00,059
to build a temple.

509
00:26:00,059 --> 00:26:01,259
And Nathan initially said,

510
00:26:01,259 --> 00:26:03,619
go and do all that was within thine heart.

511
00:26:03,619 --> 00:26:04,899
But that same night,

512
00:26:04,899 --> 00:26:06,899
the Lord appeared to Nathan and said,

513
00:26:06,899 --> 00:26:08,859
no, no, no, it's not for David

514
00:26:08,859 --> 00:26:09,979
to build the temple.

515
00:26:09,979 --> 00:26:11,899
And we find that Nathan faithfully

516
00:26:11,899 --> 00:26:14,059
went back to David and delivered the truth

517
00:26:14,059 --> 00:26:15,659
as to what David was to do.

518
00:26:15,659 --> 00:26:17,939
And you can read about the Davidic covenant

519
00:26:17,939 --> 00:26:19,219
and all that takes place

520
00:26:19,219 --> 00:26:20,699
in that portion of Scripture.

521
00:26:20,699 --> 00:26:24,339
And we find that David made it his purpose

522
00:26:24,339 --> 00:26:26,859
to prepare for the building of the temple.

523
00:26:26,859 --> 00:26:28,779
He understood that his son Solomon

524
00:26:28,779 --> 00:26:29,979
would build the temple.

525
00:26:29,979 --> 00:26:32,459
And we find that he gave liberally

526
00:26:32,459 --> 00:26:34,179
and he encouraged others to give,

527
00:26:34,179 --> 00:26:36,579
to store up all of that

528
00:26:36,579 --> 00:26:37,939
which would be necessary

529
00:26:37,939 --> 00:26:40,099
to build the temple.

530
00:26:40,099 --> 00:26:42,259
And we come to 2 Chronicles

531
00:26:42,259 --> 00:26:44,659
and we read about all that is taking place.

532
00:26:44,659 --> 00:26:47,099
We don't have time to look at all of it

533
00:26:47,099 --> 00:26:48,579
this evening, but you find that

534
00:26:48,579 --> 00:26:50,819
chapter 2 reveals to us

535
00:26:50,819 --> 00:26:53,019
some of the preparations that took place.

536
00:26:53,019 --> 00:26:55,139
And you find that in v. 4,

537
00:26:55,139 --> 00:26:55,939
the Bible says,

538
00:26:55,939 --> 00:27:00,419
behold, I build a house to the name of the Lord my God.

539
00:27:00,419 --> 00:27:02,259
We find that he says in v. 5

540
00:27:02,259 --> 00:27:04,339
of 2 Chronicles,

541
00:27:04,379 --> 00:27:06,899
and the house which I build is great.

542
00:27:06,899 --> 00:27:07,739
Why?

543
00:27:07,739 --> 00:27:11,739
For great is our God above all gods.

544
00:27:11,739 --> 00:27:13,659
We find that he says that,

545
00:27:13,659 --> 00:27:15,699
I love the phraseology that is used

546
00:27:15,699 --> 00:27:17,619
in v. 9 of chapter 2.

547
00:27:17,619 --> 00:27:19,979
He said, even to prepare me timber and abundance

548
00:27:19,979 --> 00:27:22,499
for the house which I am about to build

549
00:27:22,499 --> 00:27:25,579
shall be wonderful great.

550
00:27:25,579 --> 00:27:28,899
And you find this information that is given

551
00:27:28,899 --> 00:27:31,419
and then you read about the construction

552
00:27:31,419 --> 00:27:34,299
in chapter 3 and chapter 4

553
00:27:34,299 --> 00:27:36,739
just as you would read of the construction

554
00:27:36,739 --> 00:27:39,419
of all of the elements with regard to the tabernacle

555
00:27:39,419 --> 00:27:41,699
and those chapters leading up to

556
00:27:41,699 --> 00:27:43,379
Exodus chapter 40.

557
00:27:43,379 --> 00:27:46,059
But we come here to 2 Chronicles 5

558
00:27:46,059 --> 00:27:48,499
and we see about the dedication.

559
00:27:48,499 --> 00:27:50,979
It says in v. 1 of chapter 5,

560
00:27:50,979 --> 00:27:53,219
thus all the work that Solomon made

561
00:27:53,219 --> 00:27:54,459
for the house of the Lord,

562
00:27:54,459 --> 00:27:57,819
notice this phrase, was finished.

563
00:27:57,819 --> 00:27:59,979
What did we read about Moses

564
00:27:59,979 --> 00:28:02,339
there in Exodus 40 and v. 33?

565
00:28:02,459 --> 00:28:06,699
So Moses finished the work.

566
00:28:06,699 --> 00:28:08,739
We find here,

567
00:28:08,739 --> 00:28:10,779
the Bible says that Solomon,

568
00:28:10,779 --> 00:28:13,099
that the work that he did,

569
00:28:13,099 --> 00:28:16,179
that the house of the Lord was finished.

570
00:28:16,179 --> 00:28:19,259
We find that in v. 13,

571
00:28:19,259 --> 00:28:20,939
skip down if you will and look there,

572
00:28:20,939 --> 00:28:22,499
it says it came even to pass

573
00:28:22,499 --> 00:28:25,179
as the trumpeters and singers were as one

574
00:28:25,179 --> 00:28:27,099
to make one sound to be heard

575
00:28:27,099 --> 00:28:29,539
in praising and thanking the Lord.

576
00:28:29,539 --> 00:28:31,419
And when they lifted up their voice

577
00:28:31,459 --> 00:28:33,059
with the trumpets and cymbals

578
00:28:33,059 --> 00:28:34,579
and instruments of music

579
00:28:34,579 --> 00:28:37,739
and praised the Lord saying,

580
00:28:37,739 --> 00:28:39,500
for He is good,

581
00:28:39,500 --> 00:28:42,260
for His mercy endureth forever,

582
00:28:42,260 --> 00:28:45,579
that then, you see the word then.

583
00:28:45,579 --> 00:28:48,019
We saw that in Exodus 40

584
00:28:48,019 --> 00:28:49,459
in v. 34,

585
00:28:49,459 --> 00:28:53,179
for then the house was filled

586
00:28:53,179 --> 00:28:57,459
with a cloud, even the house of the Lord.

587
00:28:57,459 --> 00:28:59,179
So that the priests could not stand

588
00:28:59,179 --> 00:29:00,899
to minister by reason of the cloud.

589
00:29:00,899 --> 00:29:04,419
Notice, for the glory of the Lord

590
00:29:04,419 --> 00:29:09,139
had filled the house of God.

591
00:29:09,139 --> 00:29:10,859
Solomon will speak to the people.

592
00:29:10,859 --> 00:29:12,979
We see that his prayer of dedication

593
00:29:12,979 --> 00:29:16,219
is recorded as we move into chapter 6.

594
00:29:16,219 --> 00:29:18,339
And you come to chapter 7

595
00:29:18,339 --> 00:29:21,380
and you see how that prayer of dedication

596
00:29:21,380 --> 00:29:23,940
and all of the sacrifice is recorded.

597
00:29:23,940 --> 00:29:28,099
And you find the Lord replying to Solomon

598
00:29:28,099 --> 00:29:29,859
and telling him that He's heard his prayer

599
00:29:30,700 --> 00:29:32,700
But we think about the glory

600
00:29:32,700 --> 00:29:34,899
of these chapters in 2 Chronicles

601
00:29:34,899 --> 00:29:37,500
and how they mirror that which we read

602
00:29:37,500 --> 00:29:40,619
in Exodus 40.

603
00:29:40,619 --> 00:29:42,820
Something that is consistent

604
00:29:42,820 --> 00:29:45,260
in both of these events

605
00:29:45,260 --> 00:29:47,179
is the fact that the Bible says,

606
00:29:47,179 --> 00:29:49,500
then this happened.

607
00:29:49,500 --> 00:29:50,940
And it's after the obedience.

608
00:29:50,940 --> 00:29:53,419
See, Solomon obeyed that which had been

609
00:29:53,419 --> 00:29:55,219
instructed of him to do.

610
00:29:55,219 --> 00:29:57,139
And we find that Moses,

611
00:29:57,139 --> 00:29:58,859
to go back to our text of Scripture

612
00:29:58,859 --> 00:30:00,500
in Exodus chapter number 40.

613
00:30:00,500 --> 00:30:02,259
that we're studying this evening,

614
00:30:02,259 --> 00:30:04,699
we find that Moses was a faithful minister

615
00:30:04,699 --> 00:30:08,579
and Moses was an obedient servant of the Lord.

616
00:30:08,579 --> 00:30:11,119
He did that which the Lord commanded.

617
00:30:11,119 --> 00:30:15,180
This evening, what a sight it would have been

618
00:30:15,180 --> 00:30:18,139
both at the tabernacle and at the temple.

619
00:30:18,139 --> 00:30:20,319
Amazing.

620
00:30:20,319 --> 00:30:23,479
We think this evening of our own lives.

621
00:30:23,479 --> 00:30:25,559
We think of the blessing of God.

622
00:30:25,559 --> 00:30:27,920
We understand that our bodies now,

623
00:30:27,920 --> 00:30:29,379
according to the New Testament,

624
00:30:29,379 --> 00:30:30,940
the temple of the Holy Spirit,

625
00:30:30,940 --> 00:30:32,440
the Holy Ghost which is in us,

626
00:30:32,440 --> 00:30:33,599
which we have of God,

627
00:30:33,599 --> 00:30:37,840
we're not our own according to 1 Corinthians 6, verses 19 and 20.

628
00:30:37,840 --> 00:30:42,779
We find that God desires to bless His people.

629
00:30:42,779 --> 00:30:48,040
The psalmist said that He daily loatheth me with benefits.

630
00:30:48,040 --> 00:30:51,599
We find that we want then.

631
00:30:51,599 --> 00:30:53,479
We want the blessing.

632
00:30:53,479 --> 00:30:57,580
We want the desired result.

633
00:30:57,580 --> 00:30:59,240
But sometimes where we mess up

634
00:30:59,240 --> 00:31:02,220
is in that in-between area.

635
00:31:02,220 --> 00:31:05,980
We understand, and thou shalt.

636
00:31:05,980 --> 00:31:09,519
We understand the desired result.

637
00:31:09,519 --> 00:31:13,279
But sometimes we have difficulty with the do it.

638
00:31:13,279 --> 00:31:14,779
Obey it.

639
00:31:14,779 --> 00:31:16,720
Follow it.

640
00:31:16,720 --> 00:31:18,980
As the Lord commanded Moses.

641
00:31:18,980 --> 00:31:21,660
See, sometimes we're guilty of leaning on our own understanding.

642
00:31:21,660 --> 00:31:22,800
Sometimes we're guilty of saying,

643
00:31:22,800 --> 00:31:24,819
well, is that really still applicable today?

644
00:31:24,819 --> 00:31:26,900
Is that really still something we have to do today?

645
00:31:26,919 --> 00:31:27,739
Is that something?

646
00:31:27,739 --> 00:31:30,819
And we just kind of mess things up.

647
00:31:30,819 --> 00:31:32,160
And then we find ourselves in a place

648
00:31:32,160 --> 00:31:35,239
where we're not obedient like we're supposed to be,

649
00:31:35,239 --> 00:31:37,000
and we're not getting the desired result,

650
00:31:37,000 --> 00:31:38,760
and we're wondering what's going on.

651
00:31:38,760 --> 00:31:42,040
And God's saying you've got to do it My way.

652
00:31:42,040 --> 00:31:43,040
I think it's interesting.

653
00:31:43,040 --> 00:31:45,879
I understand some people could have an issue with it.

654
00:31:45,879 --> 00:31:48,580
And if you do, just remember that I didn't say it.

655
00:31:48,580 --> 00:31:49,699
J. Vernon McGee did,

656
00:31:49,699 --> 00:31:51,720
and I'm not trying to hide behind his quote.

657
00:31:51,720 --> 00:31:54,980
But I did think it was kind of interesting what he said.

658
00:31:55,639 --> 00:31:57,760
I can find fault with what he said as well.

659
00:31:57,760 --> 00:31:59,720
It's not a perfect statement.

660
00:31:59,720 --> 00:32:02,440
But J. Vernon McGee, I think on one particular occasion,

661
00:32:02,440 --> 00:32:03,800
it probably happened many times

662
00:32:03,800 --> 00:32:06,040
because he's said interesting things

663
00:32:06,040 --> 00:32:08,160
during his time in ministry

664
00:32:08,160 --> 00:32:12,919
that would reveal times of maybe frustration and annoyance.

665
00:32:12,919 --> 00:32:15,039
But I think it was one of those particular times.

666
00:32:15,039 --> 00:32:17,320
And some people were really challenging him on,

667
00:32:17,320 --> 00:32:18,699
do we really have to do that?

668
00:32:18,699 --> 00:32:20,919
And why does it have to be this way?

669
00:32:20,919 --> 00:32:23,199
And why do we have to do those things?

670
00:32:23,199 --> 00:32:25,779
And J. Vernon McGee said something to this effect.

671
00:32:25,779 --> 00:32:29,399
He said, listen, God made the world

672
00:32:29,399 --> 00:32:33,059
and God's world is God's way.

673
00:32:33,059 --> 00:32:35,100
And so if you want to do things your way,

674
00:32:35,100 --> 00:32:38,500
go create your own world and figure it out.

675
00:32:38,500 --> 00:32:40,419
I thought it was kind of comical.

676
00:32:40,419 --> 00:32:42,179
And really what's J. Vernon McGee saying?

677
00:32:42,179 --> 00:32:44,100
He's saying God is the creator.

678
00:32:44,100 --> 00:32:47,160
And he is the one that has given us the instruction book.

679
00:32:47,160 --> 00:32:49,460
He's the one that has revealed to us,

680
00:32:49,539 --> 00:32:52,320
faithfully delivered to us,

681
00:32:52,320 --> 00:32:54,339
what pleases Him.

682
00:32:54,339 --> 00:32:59,199
So ours is not to argue over the content of this book.

683
00:32:59,199 --> 00:33:01,880
Ours is simply to do it.

684
00:33:01,880 --> 00:33:04,240
Moses didn't have to take some time and say,

685
00:33:04,240 --> 00:33:07,000
well, does it really matter

686
00:33:07,000 --> 00:33:09,479
if it's placed on the left side of the holy place

687
00:33:09,479 --> 00:33:11,720
or on the right side of the holy place?

688
00:33:11,720 --> 00:33:15,039
Does it really matter if it comes before or after?

689
00:33:15,039 --> 00:33:19,199
No, no, he just had to do what God told him to do.

690
00:33:19,419 --> 00:33:21,779
And God had a reason for the placement.

691
00:33:21,779 --> 00:33:25,539
And it's God's desire

692
00:33:25,539 --> 00:33:28,220
and it's God's right to say what He wants to say.

693
00:33:28,220 --> 00:33:30,600
He's God.

694
00:33:30,600 --> 00:33:34,259
And all we have to do is obey.

695
00:33:34,259 --> 00:33:37,339
And we put it in those terms that seem so simple.

696
00:33:37,339 --> 00:33:38,580
Doesn't it?

697
00:33:38,580 --> 00:33:40,220
I mean, it really does, right?

698
00:33:40,220 --> 00:33:42,440
I remember so many times as a parent

699
00:33:42,440 --> 00:33:44,660
saying to the kids when they were younger,

700
00:33:44,660 --> 00:33:47,100
it's so simple.

701
00:33:47,100 --> 00:33:50,679
Just obey.

702
00:33:50,679 --> 00:33:53,479
And I would say it countless times.

703
00:33:53,479 --> 00:33:54,759
What is hard about this?

704
00:33:54,759 --> 00:33:55,880
Just obey.

705
00:33:55,880 --> 00:33:59,440
Just do what I said.

706
00:33:59,440 --> 00:34:02,399
Just about every single time I ever said that,

707
00:34:02,399 --> 00:34:03,800
it's as if the Holy Spirit of God

708
00:34:03,800 --> 00:34:06,360
was whispering in my ear,

709
00:34:06,360 --> 00:34:08,360
it's so easy.

710
00:34:08,360 --> 00:34:10,580
Just do what I say.

711
00:34:10,580 --> 00:34:12,880
I've given you my word.

712
00:34:12,880 --> 00:34:15,360
Just do it.

713
00:34:15,419 --> 00:34:17,339
And so many times in our life,

714
00:34:17,339 --> 00:34:19,459
we struggle with obedience.

715
00:34:19,459 --> 00:34:22,540
We make it sound easy.

716
00:34:22,540 --> 00:34:23,779
But there's challenges.

717
00:34:23,779 --> 00:34:25,739
We've got this flesh.

718
00:34:25,739 --> 00:34:28,459
We've got this reasoning.

719
00:34:28,459 --> 00:34:30,500
And this evening, when we look at the

720
00:34:30,500 --> 00:34:33,779
40th chapter of the book of Exodus,

721
00:34:33,779 --> 00:34:36,420
we see a glorious conclusion.

722
00:34:36,420 --> 00:34:40,820
Then, the glory of the Lord filled the tabernacle.

723
00:34:40,820 --> 00:34:44,859
And you read of this glorious event.

724
00:34:44,880 --> 00:34:49,880
It's a result of Moses obeying completely

725
00:34:51,959 --> 00:34:56,239
what, and thou shalt what God said.

726
00:34:56,239 --> 00:34:58,880
And this evening, if we want then,

727
00:34:58,880 --> 00:35:01,040
we better start doing.

728
00:35:01,040 --> 00:35:04,200
We need to take heed to John 2 and verse number 5.

729
00:35:04,200 --> 00:35:08,359
Whatsoever he saith unto you, do it.

730
00:35:08,359 --> 00:35:09,839
Just do it.

731
00:35:09,839 --> 00:35:12,880
Just determine that we're going to obey

732
00:35:12,880 --> 00:35:13,720
the word of God.

733
00:35:13,720 --> 00:35:15,239
Father, we love You.

734
00:35:15,239 --> 00:35:16,579
We thank You for loving us.

735
00:35:16,579 --> 00:35:18,739
Would You help us, Lord,

736
00:35:18,739 --> 00:35:22,679
to be doers of Your Word and not hearers only?

737
00:35:22,679 --> 00:35:26,480
Lord, would You help us

738
00:35:26,480 --> 00:35:29,119
to not approach Your Word

739
00:35:29,119 --> 00:35:33,119
with the thought of disagreeing

740
00:35:33,119 --> 00:35:41,839
and disputing, questioning?

741
00:35:41,839 --> 00:35:45,519
Help us to have that attitude of Moses

742
00:35:45,519 --> 00:35:47,519
as we read in this passage of Scripture,

743
00:35:47,519 --> 00:35:49,880
and thou shalt.

744
00:35:49,880 --> 00:35:51,679
Thank You, Lord,

745
00:35:51,679 --> 00:35:54,799
for giving the instruction.

746
00:35:54,799 --> 00:35:57,959
Thank You for being faithful

747
00:35:57,959 --> 00:36:01,119
to deliver to us Thy Word,

748
00:36:01,119 --> 00:36:04,679
just as You did to Moses.

749
00:36:04,679 --> 00:36:07,399
Lord, thank You that the Bible records for us

750
00:36:07,399 --> 00:36:14,519
that Moses did as You commanded.

751
00:36:14,519 --> 00:36:17,200
He obeyed.

752
00:36:17,200 --> 00:36:18,399
Thank You for the result.

753
00:36:18,399 --> 00:36:22,399
Then, the glory of the Lord filled the tabernacle.

754
00:36:22,399 --> 00:36:25,959
Lord, help us daily,

755
00:36:25,959 --> 00:36:28,079
moment by moment,

756
00:36:28,079 --> 00:36:29,799
to obey You.

757
00:36:29,799 --> 00:36:31,799
To walk in the Spirit so that we would not

758
00:36:31,799 --> 00:36:33,959
fulfill the lust of the flesh.

759
00:36:33,959 --> 00:36:35,959
To approach Your Word on a daily basis

760
00:36:35,959 --> 00:36:36,959
with that thought,

761
00:36:36,959 --> 00:36:40,160
whatsoever He saith unto You, do it.

762
00:36:40,160 --> 00:36:41,160
God, that You would help us

763
00:36:41,160 --> 00:36:43,200
to have the attitude of the psalmist.

764
00:36:43,200 --> 00:36:45,880
Lord, teach me Thy ways.

765
00:36:45,880 --> 00:36:49,920
And then help me to walk in Thy ways.

766
00:36:49,920 --> 00:36:52,559
Help us to fulfill that which we read of in James,

767
00:36:52,559 --> 00:36:54,160
that we would be doers of the Word

768
00:36:54,160 --> 00:36:56,519
and not hearers only.

769
00:36:56,519 --> 00:36:59,399
Work in hearts and lives as only You can.

770
00:36:59,399 --> 00:37:01,640
Use us, Lord, for Your honor and glory.

771
